oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Dug relics from Sequatchie County, Tennessee.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Dug relics from the Sequatchie Valley near the area of Wheeler's 1863 Raid. Items include US knapsack hooks and triangles, buttons, coins, US spur, CSA recantgular brass plate, sash or belt plate with an image, Spencer casings, brass padlock key, plain brass bridle rosettes, civilian buttons, cap from a US cavalry saber, and button studs from a saber belt.
